posts.sub: Ryback Is Waiting On Documentation Before His In-Ring Return Can Happen
posts.com:
Ryback hasn’t wrestled a match in years, but some fans would still like to see him wrestle again. For those fans keeping up hope, there is still a chance that they will see him wrestle once again, because he seems to be getting even closer after a recent legal win.

Ryback and WWE had a terrible legal dispute over his name. Since he changed his name legally, that added another layer to the situation. Now that the disagreement is in the past, it seems that Ryback is aiming at an in-ring return.

The 41-year-old former WWE Superstar recently spoke to MuscleManMalcolm, where he provided the latest update on his aspirations to make a return to the ring.

>Yeah, that’s the goal. I finally won my Ryback trademark and everything. We’re just waiting on the official documentation, which could be a few more months, but once that documentation is in my hands, we will be able to move forward and do business. I’m healthy, and I’m ready to do business.”

Ryback said that Wardlow is on his radar, of course that would require Tony Khan’s permission. We’ll have to see it Tony Khan picks up the phone for Ryback, because he hasn’t called the Big Guy yet that we know of.

2023 has already been a banner year for unexpected moments. Only time will tell if Ryback’s return to the ring will be a part of this year’s craziness.
